{
  "_comment": "Component NAME -> CPE (vendor/product) whitelist for CVE matching (Plan 1, enrich-cpe.sh). Many firmware/image components arrive with name+version but NO purl/CPE, so Trivy matches 0 CVEs. enrich-cpe.sh attaches cpe:2.3:a:<vendor>:<product>:<version>:... ONLY for names in this curated list, then Trivy matches by CPE. This is a CLOSED whitelist on purpose: a name->CPE guess for an unknown component produces FALSE-POSITIVE CVEs (a wrong vuln is worse than an empty result), so a name not listed here gets NO cpe. Keys are lower-cased component names; multiple aliases may map to the same product. vendor/product follow the NVD CPE dictionary. Entries starting with '_' are ignored.",

  "_comment_license": "Optional spdx_license per entry: the project's OFFICIAL license as an exact SPDX identifier (or a valid SPDX expression for dual/multi-license). enrich-cpe.sh fills CycloneDX licenses[] from this ONLY when the component has no license yet (syft leaves opkg/dpkg packages license-null). Accuracy is legal-grade: ONLY confirmed upstream licenses are listed, GPL '-only' vs '-or-later' is distinguished, and version-dependent or genuinely mixed packages (openssl, mbedtls, glibc, util-linux, ...) carry NO spdx_license on purpose (an empty license is safer than a wrong one).",

